nye-west-lil-pump-i-love-it-video |title=Watch Kanye West and Lil Pump's \"I Love It\" video |first=David |last=Renshaw |date=September 7, 2018 |accessdate=September 9, 2018 |publisher=The Fader}}</ref>\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| \"[[Butterfly Doors#Music video|Butterfly Doors]]\"\n| rowspan=\"3\"| 2019\n| Ben Griffin<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.rap-up.com/2019/01/05/video-lil-pump-butterfly-doors/ |title=Video: Lil Pump \u2013 'Butterfly Doors' |date=January 5, 2019 |accessdate=January 6, 2019 |publisher=Rap Up}}</ref>\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| \"[[Racks on Racks]]\"\n| BRTHR\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| \"Be Like Me\"<br />{{small|(featuring [[ Lil Wayne]])}}\n| {{Unknown}}\n|}\n\n===As featured artist===\n{| class=\"wikitable plainrowheaders\" style=\"text-align:center;\"\n|+ Music video as featured artist, showing director\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"width:15em;\"| Title\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"width:1em;\"| Year\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"width:15em;\"| Director\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| \"Nephew\"<br />{{small|(Smokepurpp featuring Lil Pump)}}\n| 2018\n| Millicent Hailes<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/hip-hop/8468815/smokepurpp-nephew-video-lil-pump |title=Smokepurpp Connects With Lil Pump in London for Menacing 'Nephew' Video: Watch |first=Michael |last=Saponara |publisher=Billboard |date=August 6, 2018 |accessdate=September 8, 2018}}</ref>\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| \"[[Poppin]]\"<br />{{small|([[KSI (entertainer)|KSI]] featuring Lil Pump and Smokepurpp)}}\n| 2020\n| TajvsTaj\n|}\n\n==Notes==\n{{notelist-ua|35em}}\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n{{Lil Pump}}\n\n[[Category:Lil Pump|Discography]]\n[[Category:Discographies of American artists]]\n[[Category:Hip hop discographies]]\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox artist discography\n| Artist          = [[Lil Pump]]\n| Image           = Lil Pump Fillmore Auditorium 05.01.19 (47761159611).jpg\n| Caption         = Lil Pump performing in May 2019\n| Alt             = \n| Studio          = 2\n| Compilation     = \n| EP              = \n| Music videos    = 16\n| Singles         = 19\n| Option          = \n| Option name     = Mixtapes\n}}\n\nAmerican rapper [[Lil Pump]] has released two [[studio album]]s, twenty-six [[Single (music)|singles]] (including five as featured artist) and sixteen [[music video]]s. In March 2016, Lil Pump released his first single, \"Elementary\". His first single to hit the ''[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]'' [[Hot 100]] was \"[[Gucci Gang]]\", debuting at number 81 and later peaked at number 3 on the chart. The single is certified four-times platinum by the [[Recording Industry of America]] (RIAA). In October 2017, he released his [[Lil Pump (album)|eponymous studio album]], peaking at number 3 on the [[Billboard 200|''Billboard'' 200]].\n\n==Studio albums==\n{| class=\"wikitable plainrowheaders\" style=\"text-align:center;\"\n|+List of studio albums, with selected chart positions, sales and certifications\n! scope=\"col\" rowspan=\"2\" style=\"width:10em;\" | Title\n! scope=\"col\" rowspan=\"2\" style=\"width:20em;\" | Album details\n! scope=\"col\" colspan=\"10\" | Peak chart positions\n! scope=\"col\" rowspan=\"2\" style=\"width:8em;\"| [[List of music recording certifications|Certifications]]\n|-\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"width:2.5em;font-size:90%;\" | [[Billboard 200|US]]<br /><ref name=BB200>{{cite web|url=http://www.billboard.com/music/lil-pump/chart-history/billboard-200|title=Lil Pump \u2013 Chart History: Billboard 200|work=[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]|accessdate=October 31, 2017}}</ref>\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"width:2.5em;font-size:90%;\" | [[Top R&B/Hip-Hop Albums|US<br />R&B/HH]]<br /><ref name=R&BHH>{{cite web|url=https://www.billboard.com/music/lil-pump/chart-history/r-b-hip-hop-albums|title=Lil Pump \u2013 Chart History: R&B/Hip-Hop Albums|work=Billboard|accessdate=October 31, 2017}}</ref>\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"width:2.5em;font-size:90%;\" | [[Ultratop|BEL]]<br /><ref>{{cite web|title=Ultratop flanders \u2013 Lil Pump (danish)|url=http://www.ultratop.be/nl/album/53a4a/Lil-Pump-Lil-Pump|accessdate=February 11, 2018}}</ref>\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"width:2.5em;font-size:90%;\" | [[Canadian Albums Chart|CAN]]<br /><ref>{{cite web|title=On The Charts: October 15, 2017|url=http://fyimusicnews.ca/articles/2017/10/15/charts-october-15-2017|accessdate=February 11, 2018}}</ref>\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"width:2.5em;font-size:90%;\" | [[The Official Finnish Charts|FIN]]<br /><ref>{{cite web|title=Suomen virallinen lista \u2013 Artistit Lil Pump|url=http://www.ifpi.fi/tilastot/virallinen-lista/artistit/Lil+Pump/Lil+Pump|accessdate=February 11, 2018}}\n* ''Harverd Dropout'': https://ifpi.fi/tilastot/virallinen-lista/albumit/2019/9</ref>\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"width:2.5em;font-size:90%;\" | [[Syndicat National de l'\u00c9dition Phonographique|FRA]]<br /><ref>{{cite web|url=https://lescharts.com/showinterpret.asp?interpret=Lil+Pump|title=Discographie Lil Pump|website=lescharts.com|accessdate=July 20, 2019}}</ref>\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"width:2.5em;font-size:90%;\" | [[Federazione Industria Musicale Italiana|ITA]]<br /><ref>{{cite web|url=https://italiancharts.com/showitem.asp?interpret=Lil+Pump&titel=Lil+Pump&cat=a|title=Lil Pump - Lil Pump|website=italiancharts.com|accessdate=July 20, 2019}}</ref>\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"width:2.5em;font-size:90%;\" | [[MegaCharts|NL]]<br /><ref>{{cite web|title=duchcharts.nl \u2013 Lil Pump|url=http://www.dutchcharts.nl/showitem.asp?interpret=Lil+Pump&titel=Lil+Pump&cat=a|accessdate=February 11, 2018}}</ref>\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"width:2.5em;font-size:90%;\" | [[Official New Zealand Music Chart|NZ]]<br /><ref name=\"NZ\">{{cite web|url=https://charts.nz/showinterpret.asp?interpret=Lil+Pump|title=Discography Lil Pump|website=charts.nz|accessdate=July 20, 2019}}</ref>\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"width:2.5em;font-size:90%;\" | [[Sverigetopplistan|SWE]]<br /><ref name=\"SWE\">{{cite web|url=http://www.swedishcharts.com/showinterpret.asp?interpret=Lil+Pump|title